com.gams.api

Class GAMSExecutionException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com.gams.api.GAMSException
            • com.gams.api.GAMSExecutionException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GAMSExecutionException
extends GAMSException
    GAMSExecutionException contains the exit code unsuccessfully returned by GAMS process. For instance, within GAMSJob.run() method, this exception will be thrown if GAMS process terminates with an error (exit code that is not '0'). GAMSExecutionException extends GAMSException which subclasses Java Runtime Exception; therefore, it can be thrown during the normal operation of the Java Virtual Machine.
    See Also:
    GAMSGlobals.ExitCodeMessage, Serialized Form
